3. Full Pipeline Dry Run (Mock Mode)
Fast end-to-end with mock data:

```bash
cd /workspace/mldojo && .venv/bin/python main.py --mock --fast
```

This runs the full pipeline in mock mode (no LLM calls, no subprocess). Should complete in ~1 minute.

---

4. Real End-to-End (LLM + Execution)
The full real test — requires LLM API access and sklearn:

```bash
cd /workspace/mldojo && .venv/bin/python main.py --task-desc input/description.md --fast
```

This will:
- Call the LLM via Ollama Cloud to retrieve 4 sklearn models
- Call the LLM to generate code for each model
- Execute each candidate script in a subprocess
- Run through the full search → ensemble → submission flow
Estimated time: 10-30 minutes depending on LLM speed and number of models.


---

```bash
.venv/bin/python main.py \
  --task-desc input/description.md \
  --num-parallel-solutions 2 \
  --max-full-cycles 3
```

---

Total LLM-heavy operations per full cycle with 2 parallel pipelines:
- Search: 2 models × 2 pipelines = 4 A2__generate + 4 A13__check + 4 A12__check + eval/debug
- Ablation: 2 outer × 1 ablation × 2 pipelines = 2 A4__generate_ablation + 2× eval/debug
- Refinement: 2 outer × 2 inner = 4 A7__implement + 4× eval/debug per pipeline
- Ensemble: 2 rounds
- Leakage fixes: up to 2 retries per check
The CLI invocation would be:

```bash
MLE_EXECUTION_MAX_CPU_SECONDS=1800 \
MLE_EXECUTION_TIMEOUT=900 \
MLE_MAX_OUTER_STEPS=2 \
MLE_MAX_INNER_STEPS=2 \
MLE_MAX_ENSEMBLE_ROUNDS=2 \
MLE_NUM_RETRIEVED_MODELS=2 \
MLE_MAX_DEBUG_RETRIES=2 \
MLE_MAX_ABLATION_DEBUG_RETRIES=2 \
MLE_MAX_ENSEMBLE_DEBUG_RETRIES=2 \
MLE_MAX_LEAKAGE_FIX_RETRIES=2 \
.venv/bin/python main.py \
  --task-desc input/description.md \
  --num-parallel-solutions 2 \
  --max-full-cycles 2
```
